Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Yakutsk, Yoshino, you two okay!?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yes, somehow. We would have been in danger if we had been a bit further away from everyone.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Yakutsk, so what happened to those boys?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: As it turns out, those boys were not people. They were just a kind of illusion that appeared with the Phantom Mist.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: They called themselves Karl and Emil. They lied about being lost, yet they seemed to know something about these ruins.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Are they Mist Monsters that lurks in these ruins?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Well, apparently not. I'm pretty sure they called the trenches and tochka the 'defensive lines', but it appears they were looking for a way to avoid these ruins. They wanted to get through to the west without going through the ruins...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: They took Yoshino's map, Yakutsk tried to catch them but they disappeared like a puff of smoke.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: It could be a trap to lure intruders out of the ruins. Or it could have been intended to split us.

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Hey! Stop dawdling, we're going back to the ruins! No matter how many enemies we vanquished outside here, there's no signs of the Phantom Mist disappearing!

Name: Amiens
Phrase: I knew it, the Ouvrage Schoenenbourg is the source of the Phantom Mist! We have to find a solution inside the ruins!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: If we don't do something quickly, the ruins will grow increasingly bigger... Will the gendarmerie deployed in the forest be enough to hold them? Should we retreat for now and call for reinforcements from the main army...?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Vivienne, it's okay. Compared to Nishiki's Ningyou Jigoku, This is nothing. Verforet is your hometown, Vivienne, it shouldn't be a scary place for you right?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Besides, Amiens and Rouen have explored plenty of ruins, haven't they? Even the progress of attacking this Ouvrage Schoenenbourg is going well so far.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Putra...

Name: Putra
Phrase: Let's continue investigating the ruins. I'm sure we'll find the source of the Phantom Mist. Then the Mist Monsters in the forest will disappear.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Am I right?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Oui, guess so...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: That's right, let's stop caring about Karl and Emil! Let's do what we can do now!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: If we're going to retreat, now is the time! Let's head back to the ruins!

Name: Putra
Phrase: Whoa! We've only been away for a minute and there's already so much Mist! It's going to be hard to find the source of this outbreak...

Name: Rouen
Phrase: The source of the Phantom Mist, if there is one, is at the far end of the ruins. The last stronghold is where the master of these ruins waits.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: But the structure of these ruins makes it difficult to identify the 'far end'. The extensive labyrinth, the exit to the surface... Is the key, after all, the rails in the tunnels?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Um, may I have a word!?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: What's wrong, Paddington?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: That steel minecart over there, it's not the same one that Yoshino found in the first place. I don't know how it got there, but it's been replaced by another cart!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Huh? But it looks the same to me...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: No, it's definitely not the same minecart as the one that was there. Some sections have different rust marks, and there are some scratches on the body. These scratches were not on the cart that was there earlier.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: If Paddington says so, then it must be so.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: But what does the switch mean then?

Name: Putra
Phrase: The cart that was just there has moved to another place. In conjunction with that, the cart that was stopped in another place ran to this place.

Name: Putra
Phrase: This is not the type that is manned by crew. There's a power source somewhere that's moving the carts and the rails in a certain area.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: That power source is from mist stones, right? Can the mist stone's magic be controlled that well...?

Name: Putra
Phrase: There's a similar system like this inside the Flamarinian mines. But it's state-of-the-art tech that's only available in a few key facilities. It's not the kind of tech that's been around for a long time.

Name: Putra
Phrase: It's impossible to move a number of minecarts over such a large area with just the magic power of mist stones. That's exactly why I think it's difficult unless you combine a power source on the level of the Mist Core with the magic power of a Divine Child, like the Mist Train...

Name: Putra
Phrase: Conductor, what do you think? Do you feel anything from this rail?
At Putra's suggestion, I lightly touched the minecart and rails to see if there was any magic power derived from mist stones there, or to see if I could sense any other special power.
However, the touch feels like it is just regular steel. I cannot feel the flow of magic power from the metal, and it does not seem to resonate with my magic power.

However, I share the same opinion as Putra. I think there is a power source somewhere that is operating the mechanisms of these ruins. The alarms sound and the lights come on because there is a power source.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: If there is a master of these ruins, it's where the power source is. Somewhere it's controlling the whole mechanism of the ruins.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Let's find the room where the power source is. If we follow the rails, we'll get there.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: The question is which rail to follow...
Intruders Have Breached The Defence Line! Maintain Ouvrage Schoenenbourg! Now Is The Time To Demonstrate How Strong The Defenders Of Maginot Are!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: It's that voice again! Is that the master of the ruins?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Hey, look! There's a minecart coming at us from the other side!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Iron minecart, gatan goton. High-speed train, gatan goton.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Well, it's a cart and it doesn't travel fast...

Name: Putra
Phrase: Wait why the heck is this cart going so faaast! Yoshino, get out of the way!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Oooooh?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Everyone, move away, move away! It's going to derail if it runs into us at that speed!

Name: Putra
Phrase: It's trying to kill us! It ran into us at non-braking speed!?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: But it's useful as a means of transportation.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Yeah, provided that you have brakes, though...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: It's dangerous to ride this thing as long as we don't know how to operate it. I don't know if it's actually meant to go that fast.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: The minecart just came uphill, didn't it? Going downhill is fine enough, but can a steel cart go uphill at that speed?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Maybe the master of the ruins put us up to it. That trolley is also a trap to keep intruders out.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: So you think there might be a power source at the end of that rail?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: I can't say for sure, but I think it's very likely.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: So you're saying that the cart bombed.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: It can carry both bombs and people. When the site was inhabited, they may have sent soldiers to the intruders.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Do you think it's possible... to carry Phantom Mist instead of people?

Name: Amiens
Phrase: Non, not possible.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: ...This minecarts seems to be generating Phantom Mist!

Name: Putra
Phrase: What do you think, Vivienne, if we keep fighting here, we're doing what they want us to do, aren't we?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Of course not, we won't let them slow us down. Let's keep moving forward!

Name: Putra
Phrase: That's the way to go!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: If we stop here, they'll send more and more reinforcements. Amiens and Rouen take the front, Yakutsk and Yoshino in the rear.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Tch! Get lost!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Everyone, get to the tunnel now! I'll take care of the back, just keep going!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Leave your buttocks to Yoshino and Yakutsk~
The Phantom Mist generated by the minecarts that rushes into the tunnel at high speed quickly covered the narrow tunnel.
Led by Vivienne, the Special Steel Squad ran down the long, long descent, following the rails that extended underground, while knocking down the attacking Mist Monsters.
